A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 36-74-30 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 other enforcement methods and probable cause for investigation required, so as to provide
3 for investigations or inspections of certain residential rental property when there is a
4 reasonable suspicion of a code violation; to provide for the registration of certain residential
5 rental property; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other
6 purposes.
7 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
8 SECTION 1.
9 Code Section 36-74-30 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to other
10 enforcement methods and probable cause for investigation required, is amended by revising
11 subsection (b) as follows:
12 "(b) No local government is authorized to perform investigations or inspections of
13 residential rental property unless there is probable cause to believe there is or has been a
14 violation or violations of applicable codes, and in no event may a local government require
15 the registration of residential rental property. Conditions which appear to be code
16 violations which are in plain view may form the basis for probable cause.
