17 (b)(1) With adequate notice to the owner, a local government is authorized to perform
18 investigations or inspections of residential rental property containing four or more
19 dwelling units when there is a reasonable suspicion to believe there is or has been a
20 violation or violations of applicable codes. Conditions which appear to be code
21 violations and are in plain view may form the basis for a reasonable suspicion.
22 (2) A local government may require the registration of residential rental property owned
23 directly or indirectly by any person or entity that owns at least 20 residential rental
24 properties in Georgia."
25 SECTION 2.
26 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
